page.title: 06WOODLANDS,NEWTON ST.CYRES.
page.content: Most people who live in Woodlands find there are{no disadvantages.}Even though there are{28 houses}in Woodlands it is very{quiet.} The older people in Woodlands think there should be more shops in the village.The people are{friendly. { Behind most of}the houses are pastures and meadows which the residents like.It is said by some people in Woodlands that the gardens are not big enough.The{noise from the {Parish Hall}is sometimes annoying. The houses are quite small so there is a limit on how big your pets can be.Sometimes when the children are playing, the ball goes into other people's gardens and they get cross.The houses in Woodlands are numbered.Each house has a{garage}which they find very useful,and{seven to {eight rooms.
